       "            strategy\n",
       "            <span class=\"param-doc-description\">strategy: {\"most_frequent\", \"prior\", \"stratified\", \"uniform\",             \"constant\"}, default=\"prior\"<br><br>Strategy to use to generate predictions.<br><br>* \"most_frequent\": the `predict` method always returns the most<br>  frequent class label in the observed `y` argument passed to `fit`.<br>  The `predict_proba` method returns the matching one-hot encoded<br>  vector.<br>* \"prior\": the `predict` method always returns the most frequent<br>  class label in the observed `y` argument passed to `fit` (like<br>  \"most_frequent\"). ``predict_proba`` always returns the empirical<br>  class distribution of `y` also known as the empirical class prior<br>  distribution.<br>* \"stratified\": the `predict_proba` method randomly samples one-hot<br>  vectors from a multinomial distribution parametrized by the empirical<br>  class prior probabilities.<br>  The `predict` method returns the class label which got probability<br>  one in the one-hot vector of `predict_proba`.<br>  Each sampled row of both methods is therefore independent and<br>  identically distributed.<br>* \"uniform\": generates predictions uniformly at random from the list<br>  of unique classes observed in `y`, i.e. each class has equal<br>  probability.<br>* \"constant\": always predicts a constant label that is provided by<br>  the user. This is useful for metrics that evaluate a non-majority<br>  class.<br><br>  .. versionchanged:: 0.24<br>     The default value of `strategy` has changed to \"prior\" in version<br>     0.24.</span>\n",
